text: Islamia collegiateIslamia collegiate groundIslamia collegiate ground Islamia Collegiate School is a school in Peshawar, Khyber Pakhtunkhwa, Pakistan, founded in 1913 by Sahibzada Abdul Qayyum and Sir George Roose Keppel. It is a part of Islamia College Peshawar. The School has a history of hundred years. It has lush green gardens and huge grounds. Every year more than 1500 students graduate from here. == References == Category:Schools in Peshawar
